# ANTA BHFA MicroSite - Design System Rules (Mobile-First)

**Source:** [Figma Design - Mobile View](https://www.figma.com/design/ifTYSKlWj1kfrZbyU0OrDG/ANTA?node-id=213-3)  
**Last Updated:** 2025-01-27  
**Breakpoint:** Mobile views (`<sm` / `<640px`)

---

## Overview

This document defines the design system rules for implementing mobile views (`<sm` breakpoint) based on the Figma design specifications. These rules ensure consistency when converting Figma designs to Astro + Tailwind CSS code.

**Technology Stack:**
- **Framework:** Astro with TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (utility-first)
- **Design Tokens:** `src/lib/design-tokens.ts`
- **Font System:** Custom fonts (ANTA/NIKE, Sharp Grotesk variants)

---

## 1. Mobile Breakpoint Definition

**Breakpoint:** `<sm` (screens < 640px)

**Implementation Pattern:**
```astro
<!-- Mobile-first: Base styles apply to mobile -->
<div class="text-[14px] md:text-[18px]">
  Content
</div>
```

**Key Principle:** All base styles (without breakpoint prefixes) apply to mobile. Use `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` for larger screens.

